# Wedding planning app — design system (Soft stack C1)

## Canonical sources (in order)

1. **`app/globals.css`** — canonical for **token VALUES**. If a hex disagrees with any document,
   `globals.css` wins.
2. **`wedding-app/.cursor/design.mdc`** (this file) — canonical for **RULES**. If a rule disagrees
   with any document, this file wins.
3. **`design/reference.html`** — a **rendered example** of these rules. Non-normative. It is
   regenerated to match; it never defines.
4. **`design/theme-direction.html`** — **superseded; scheduled for deletion in STYLE-01.**
5. The Project Bible §10 — a **pointer** to this file. It must not restate token values or rules.
   Any §10 content that contradicts this file is stale by definition.

`main.mdc` (beside this file) is canonical for **architecture** — multi-tenancy, RLS-as-sole-
authorization, data-access conventions. This file governs **visual design only** and defers to
`main.mdc` on everything else. Neither file restates the other.

---

## Direction: "Soft stack" (C1)

A calm, fast tool organized by **depth**. The canvas is a tinted mauve wash; raised white cards
lift off it; recessed wells hold rows and tracks. Hierarchy is encoded by raised-contains-recessed
— never by decoration, never by stacking raised inside raised. Type is all-sans Figtree on Tier 1
and Tier 2; romance lives in the data and in Tier 3 website templates, not in chrome serifs.

Tokens below are the **target** Soft stack set. Live values in `app/globals.css` still reflect
Modern romantic v3 until STYLE-01 applies them. Until then, `globals.css` remains canonical for
what the app actually renders; this file is canonical for what rules require.

