## Surface taxonomy (three tiers)

Every UI decision belongs to exactly one tier. Tier rules **permit** what lower tiers forbid;
global hard don'ts (below) still apply everywhere unless a tier explicitly carves out.

### Tier 1 — App chrome (Soft stack)

**Where:** **Tier 1 is everything not explicitly named Tier 2 or Tier 3.** Named exclusions:
`components/website/` (Tier 3); `components/marketing/`, the onboarding hero, and empty-state
heroes (Tier 2). Everything else — including `app/login/`, `app/styleguide/`, all project tabs,
dashboards, forms, tables, the seating builder, the assistant panel, and the print run sheet —
is Tier 1.

**Palette** (full replacement of the Modern romantic chrome set; does **not** touch `--ws-*`):

| Token | Value | Job |
|---|---|---|
| `--canvas` | `#F3EEF0` | page background (tinted, never white) |
| `--surface` | `#FFFFFF` | raised card |
| `--well` | `#F7F3F5` | recessed row / track / inner well |
| `--ink` | `#241C20` | primary text |
| `--muted` | `#857A80` | secondary text, labels, meta |
| `--hairline` | `#EFE7EB` | in-card dividers only |
| `--ring` | `#DCD0D6` | control outlines (inputs, checkboxes, seating stroke) |
| `--accent` | `#C0396B` | selection, active chip, committed bar, links |
| `--accent-wash` | `#FBEEF3` | accent tint background |
| `--sage` | `#2F6B54` | done / booked / signed / accepted / rsvp-yes |
| `--clay` | `#B0762E` | in progress / sent / contacted / proposal |
| `--clay-wash` | `#FBF1E2` | clay pill background |
| `--rosewood` | `#C4453F` | overdue / over-plan / lost / declined / rsvp-no |
| `--rosewood-wash` | `#FDECEB` | rosewood pill background |

**Renames / retirements (deliberate):**
- `--plum` → **`--accent`** (value is berry; old name would lie).
- `--stone` and `--stone-soft` are **retired** and split into `--hairline` / `--ring` / `--well`.
  One name may not carry four jobs (hairline, outline, track/well, soft wash).
- `--porcelain`, `--ink-soft`, `--ink-muted`, `--plum-deep`, `--plum-tint`, `--rose`,
  `--surface-2` are retired from the chrome vocabulary; use `--canvas`, `--muted`,
  `--accent` / `--accent-wash`, `--surface` / `--well` as appropriate.
- Status-colour **meaning** is unchanged: sage = settled, clay = in flight, rosewood = wrong,
  `--well` / `--muted` = neutral. Kind is never encoded in a status colour.

**Depth scale — exactly two levels. There is no third.**

| Level | Token | Value | On |
|---|---|---|---|
| Raised | `--shadow-raised` | `0 1px 2px rgba(60,30,45,.05), 0 10px 30px -8px rgba(60,30,45,.11)` | `--surface` (cards, phase groups, rail cards, progress band) |
| Recessed | `--shadow-recessed` | `inset 0 1px 2px rgba(60,30,45,.06)` | `--well` (task rows, tracks, inner wells) |

Depth encodes hierarchy: a raised thing contains recessed things. Depth is never decorative and
never stacks — **no raised card inside a raised card.** Replaces `--card-shadow`.

**Radius — three values, no others.** Ad-hoc Tailwind radius utilities are banned on Tier 1.

| Token | Value | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `--radius-card` | `22px` | cards / raised surfaces |
| `--radius-inner` | `14px` | inner wells / recessed rows |
| `--radius-pill` | `999px` | pills and bars |

Replaces `--radius: 12px` / `--radius-lg: 16px`.

**Type — all sans.** `--font-sans` is Figtree, weights **400 / 500 / 600 / 800**.

| Role | Size | Weight | Tracking |
|---|---|---|---|
| h1 | 42px (32px below 900w) | 800 | −.03em |
| Big number (%, stat figures, counts) | 52px | 800 | −.035em |
| Card / phase / section title | 19px | 800 | −.02em |
| Body / row title | 15px | 500 | — |
| Label | 14px | 500 | — |
| Meta / tiny | 13px | 400 | — |
| Eyebrow | 12px | 600 | .09em, uppercase |

Money and count numerals: `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`.

**Eyebrow (chrome):** 12px / 600, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.09em, color `--accent`. No diamond.

**Accent floods:** Tier 1 permits **no accent flood at all**. `--accent-wash` is for pills and
small washes only — never a full-page or full-panel color field.

**Seating canvas** follows this depth scale: tables are raised `--surface` on `--canvas`; outlines
read `--ring`.

**Print run sheet (`RunSheetDocument.tsx`) — Tier 1 with a serif carve-out.**
It reads the Tier 1 palette, radius, depth, and body type (`--font-sans`) like any other chrome
surface. **The one exception:** its print header couple-names `h1` (the only element that uses
`font-display` today) may use Cormorant (`--font-serif`). Date, venue, owner subtitle, section
labels, event rows, chrome controls, and footer stay sans. Nothing else on it may use serif.
**Why the exception survives:** it is a printed artifact carrying the couple's names, handed to
vendors. It is the one place a serif earns its keep, and TL-02 already shipped and verified it.
**Why it is not Tier 3:** it is authenticated, internal, and has no `--ws-*` namespace. Palette
isolation was never something it had — only serif permission.

### Tier 2 — Emotional surfaces

**Where (exhaustive — a surface not on this list is Tier 1):** the landing route and
`components/marketing/` in full; the onboarding hero / welcome moments; and empty-state heroes
(centered first-impression moments — not inline list empties inside a tab). Tier 2 is the
**route**, not the hero — a boundary that runs *through* a page gets re-litigated on every slice
that touches it, and "exactly one deep field per surface" is meaningless unless "surface" means a
whole page.

Tier 2 uses **Tier 1's palette and typeface** (Figtree). What it gains:

- Display numerals / headlines may run to **~104px**, weight 800, tracking −.05em.
- **Exactly one** deep field per surface: `#3D2430`, radius `28px`, shadow
  `0 18px 44px -14px rgba(61,36,48,.45)`. One per surface (whole route), not one per section.
- `--card-shadow-emotional` remains available for emotional-surface cards only (Tier 2).
- **No serif.** Tier 2 does not get Cormorant.

**Still banned on emotional surfaces:** florals, photographic assets, metal/gold gradients,
heavy glow, stacked depth, more than one deep field per surface.

### Tier 3 — Website templates

**Where:** `components/website/` (public sites at `/w/[slug]`) — **and nothing else.**

Tier 3 is public, couple-branded, and guest-facing. It gets both an isolated palette (`--ws-*`) and
a display-type carve-out (Cormorant, Great Vibes) because it is a **separate visual product** from
the app, not because it is decorative. A surface that needs only one of those two things is not
Tier 3.

**Entirely unchanged by the Soft stack chrome pivot.** Colour continues to come only from
`--ws-*` tokens, which are **separate from and unaffected by** the Tier 1 tokens above.
Body sans is **`--ws-font-sans`** (Hanken Grotesk 400/500) — parallel to the `--ws-*` colour
namespace, not the chrome sans variable; it scopes to `components/website/` only. Cormorant
Garamond and Great Vibes are sanctioned on this surface (Great Vibes here only; Cormorant also has
the Tier 1 print-header carve-out). `components/website/` continues to import no
Supabase/auth/server-only modules.

> **Websites read `--ws-*` only — colour AND type. Tier 1 Soft stack tokens, including the chrome
> sans face, are never consumed on Tier 3.**

**Bounded-decorative carve-out (unchanged from 3.7a/3.7b):**
- Restrained templates (`Classic`, `Editorial`, `Minimalist`, `Garden`) stay on `--ws-*` theme
  tokens + Cormorant + sans (`--ws-font-sans`).
- Decorative templates (`Romance`, and similar) may expand vocabulary **within bounds:**
  - **Great Vibes** (`font-script`) — Romance template only, for a single script accent element.
  - CSS/SVG ornaments (hairline + diamond/dot divider) — no image assets.
  - Warmer palette via theme tokens (`blush`, etc.) — low-saturation, never a blush flood.
  - At most one non-app display face (Great Vibes on Romance). Cormorant italic ampersand is
    the fallback when script is not used.
- Still hard-banned even in decorative templates: floral/photographic ornament image assets,
  gold/metal gradients, drop-shadow bling, blush color floods.

