## Migrated from Project Bible §10

These decisions lived only in the Bible; they belong here so rules have a single home:

- **No pie charts, no donuts, no circular progress on the budget page.** Category share is
  decorative; a filled circle is a colour flood.
- **Budget bars reuse the checklist progress-band vocabulary** — two pages, one product.
- **Seating: table kind is distinguished by form and text only, never by a status colour.**
- **Seating: full occupancy = `--sage`; selection = `--accent`.**
- **Seating canvas follows the Tier 1 depth scale** — tables are raised `--surface` on
  `--canvas`; outlines read `--ring`.
- **No florals, no gold/metal gradients, no photographic image assets on Tier 1 or Tier 2.**

