## Hard don'ts (global drift watchlist)

These apply on **every tier** unless a tier carve-out explicitly permits otherwise.

- No floral graphics.
- No photographic ornament assets.
- No gold/metal gradients.
- No Tier 1 accent floods (see Tier 1 / Tier 2 flood rules above).
- No heavy glow or decorative (non-hierarchical) shadows.
- No raised-inside-raised stacking on Tier 1.
- No ad-hoc radius utilities on Tier 1 — use `--radius-card` / `--radius-inner` / `--radius-pill`.

**App chrome + Tier 2 — additionally:**
- No Cormorant or Great Vibes (location rule) — except the Tier 1 print-header carve-out for
  Cormorant on the run sheet.
- No script fonts.

**Tier 3 website — additionally:**
- Great Vibes stays Romance-template-only.
- Decorative expansion = script accent + CSS ornament + warmer `--ws-*` theme tokens only.
- Do not import or reuse Tier 1 Soft stack tokens (colour or type, including `--font-sans`);
  websites read `--ws-*` only — colour AND type.

